6. DETERMINISTIC DERATING FORMULA

To calculate the exact saving for your specific deployment:

Saving (%) =
100 × (1 − (E_active + E_leakage + E_refresh + E_idle) / Baseline_Energy)

Where:

· E_active = 0.02 nJ (Basic) or 1.45 nJ (Improved)
· E_leakage = 0.5–1.5 nJ (depends on node size, e.g., 5nm vs 28nm)
· E_refresh = 0.2–0.4 nJ (depends on SRAM capacity)
· E_idle = 0.1–0.3 nJ (depends on FSM state retention)

For the Improved version, the Transformer's larger silicon footprint increases leakage disproportionately—hence the ~1–2% absolute drop.

